Well I've decided that it's time for another change in my life.  So I have created a new Live Journal, and will be "moving" into it.  There are several reasons for this, and one day I may be able to articulate them enough to explain.

I plan to update alot more often on this new journal (no really, I do plan to), and hopefully make a few more friends.  I'll even have multiple userpics (gasp!).

So goodbye Redchristoph.  Hello Zakzahn.

I'm going to be running a new campaign on Monday nights, named Undying: In Nomine.  It is an action/horror game along the lines of Call of Cthulu meets In Nomine.  I'm looking for one or two more players.

I have a website for it at http://zakzahn.s2hack.com/Undying/

If you are interested or have any questions, email me at Zakzahn@gmail.com

At home sick.  Blegh.  And work dosn't believe me so I have to go and get a doctor's certificate.  Blgeh.

Codym's Undying campaign finished last night, with a big epic battle.  Jonathan developed a sudden case of caution, and survived the battle, but my character ended up with his soul stuck in a magical pendent.  However, the "good guys" won, the bad guys were soundly defeated, and much fun and gore was had by all.

"Blegh"

Well, I'm just packing to go and visit the family for Christmas.  It'll be good to get away for a few days, especially from the madhouse that work has become.  Each day strengthens my resolve to begin looking for a new job after the silly season.

Mmmmmm... breakfeast.

Gaming News:  Vahkan is going okay.  We are on a quest to free our ship from an island/shell that rose up and trapped it.  It's been interesting so far, hopefully will continue to be.  Undying Souls is winding down, with the next session probably to be the last.  We are at the final battle ground, and our temporary allies (who we were planning to backstab) have backstabed us, just as another enemy is on the way.  But that's okay really, because we want them all in the same place at the same time anyway, as part of a ritual type thing to get the Undying King out of me without my having to die.  Saltmarsh is coming together.  The party are on a ship looking for a specific chest to return to their employer, and have been thouroughly poisoned by the various spiders (oh no, it's a giant spider) that inhabit the ship.  The session ended with <lj user="codym"> down on 0 strength, most of the party on low strength scores, and them battling a Half-Orc druid, and his snake animal companion.

Oh well, better get back to eating and packing.

Merry Christmas

Zakzahn

Well I'm currently at home (home home) attending my dad's 50th birthday, and catching up with family I havn't seen in a while.  Will be a good break.

My new campaign seems to be going well, with the party trying to establish themselves in the town, looking to make some money, and figure out what to do with a run down building one of them has inherited.
I must get to work on possible "quest" type things for them.  Money making ventures and the like.

I've completely redone the website for the new campaign, giving it what I think is a better look.  May be moving it to a new domain if <lj user="Codym"> and I end up going halves in buying one.

Undying is going well, so long as Jason can keep the very powerful artifact he's aquired.  With that we may have a chance.

Tuesday is going okay.  I think Micheal needs to provide a few more challenging encounters.  And perhaps a few that we can't just talk our way out of, because that happens almost every time.

Well, that's all I can think of now, although we need more parties, damn it.  Hey, everyone, host more parties.

Well, that was the last ever session of my Invasion campaign, which has been going for about a year and a quater now. The party destroyed the link between their world and the invading one, killed a Balor, killed the king of the Elves (it's ok, he wanted to die), split up (which would have gotten them killed), got back together, and killed the chosen of the goddess of the drow (a Fang of "Llolth" Drow Paragon). We then went through alot of what happened after the war, with being immortal and queen of the Elves, becoming crown prince of the Dwarves, ruling the port city of his homeland, Nardo clensing a dark forest and living there, and learning the ways of the Greenbond and travelling the world, seeing its wonders, and protecting the weak. Now I get to focus on the upcoming Saltmarsh campaign, and finishing the rules. And I get time off this weekend. Woot!

Well wasn't that a fun party.  Dancing, Dancing, and even more dancing.  A pity that some of the songs were played a second time, but at least they were good songs.  Didn't really get to talk to many peoples, but that's what happens when there is a pretty good play list.  Did get quite squiffy from the alcohol though.  Didn't even get to maudilin because of it.
Got home about 3.30am, no, 4.30am (daylight savings) after walking home with <lj user="venomcat">, <lj user="keltickat"> and <lj user="eladrin"> which distracted me from my poor sore legs.

Going to see Wallace and Grommit this afternoon with <lj user="codym"> and <lj user="kiwired">, which should be fun and amusing.

"Everybody knows the moon is made of cheese... "

Well, work is about to get a whole lot harder now.  The other guy who worked in the department with me (and was essentially my supervisor) has resigned, moving onto greener pastures and all, leaving me essentially by myself.  My boss is going to take over his paperwork (thank heavens) but that still means that all the shelf stocking will have to be done by me (unles the boss lends a hand, but that's unknown at this point).  
Also, my days have been changed.  I now work from Tuesday to Saturday, so I get the busy Fridays and Saturdays.  Yay.

Today went by much to fast.  Probably the last holdiay I'll have in a while. :(

"The future, according to some scientists, will be exactly like the past, only far more expensive."

.... I'm going to miss the Bordello cooling party.  I'm going down to visit my parents for the weekend.  There is finally a party, and I'm going to miss it.

:(

"grumble mumble grumble... dynamite"

Went and saw Charlie and the Chocolate Factory tonight.  Overall it was fun, but it had a few niggling problems.
One - The love child of Jango Fett, AKA the Oompa Loompas
Two - Ooompa Loompas are terrible singers, and dancers, and... anything to do with music really.
Three - It focused on Willy Wonka far to much, it's supposed to be CHARLIE and the Chocolate Factory.
I could go on, but I won't.
It was fun though, but more fun in the way that Bride and Predjudice was fun.  You just find youself groaning out loud, and yet still having fun.  The self referential jokes were kind of amusing, and pointing out the silliness of the Oompa Loompas bursting it to song was kinda brilliant.
Overall, 7/10.

At least I had good company to watch it with.  Thanks <lj user="the_legionnaire"> and <lj user="el_gremmo"> for a good night out.

"I'm sorry, I was having a flashback"

PS. Oh and can't forget the cameo by Darth Tyranical Dentist.

I now have a desktop computer, all though it is currently a table top.  Little bit of shopping around, and some advice from friends (<lj user="codym"> and <lj user="eskermikey">) I found one that will do what I want, and not cost toooo much.  Now I can play all these fun games I have acces to, surf the internet, and do funky stuff for my roleplaying games.

I also have a new Message Board for my upcoming campaign, mostly discussing the rules variant I will be using, but other things as well.  It will hopefully be useful.

The Election.  We had one.  Give it a few weeks and we will know what actually happened.

Tired.  Sleep.  Zzzzzz.

For The Record:

A Nerd is someone who is passionate about learning/being smart/academia.
A Geek is someone who is passionate about some particular area or subject, often an obscure or difficult one.
A Dork is someone who has difficulty with common social expectations/interactions.
You scored better than half in Dork, earning you the title of: Pure Dork. Like our friends Napoleon Dynamite & co.

It's not as though you were some whiz-kid in school. Oh, sure, you probably did okay in some classes, but were probably awful in others. Certainly most people thought you were smarter than you thought yourself to be. And it's not that you have some overriding passion, like computers or Star Trek that sets you apart for the crowd, though you likely share some interest in some of those sorts of things. You just like to be yourself, and want to express yourself for who you are.

And, really, there's nothing wrong with that. Being who you are often invites scorn, and so it's a difficult thing in a world that rewards conformity. Be proud of your dorkiness, for often it's just another word for individuality. (I'd vote for you!)

Congratulations!

 "We're not monsters, we're moral people"

Well, had Buckets of Dice in the weekend. Didn't get to play in anything unfortunately, but got to run a game I hurriedly put together over the last week called Monsters at the Door. The players were a bunch of Ghouls in an army, sent in behind enemy lines to clear a mansion of enemy soldiers. The hard part was that the Commander didn't want the enemy to find out who had killed all their soldiers, so the players would have to be careful and sneaky. The party did pretty well, just unfortunate that we ran out of time, as they had just found a method that would have got the job done. They had spent alot of time luring out small patrols and killing them, and got a little too focused on trying to weaken or wipe out the place with a disease from their cleric's Contagion spell, but I think they had fun trying to puzzle out the best way to kill off the enemy. Alas, it is now time to go to bed, with the warmth and the sleeping. Good night all.

Well wasn't that fun. My party has just faced the legendary Tarrasque, and won. It was a large fight in which most of the party at one time or another were eaten, but were able to escape mere rounds before death because the beast was taken down. Of course he got back up, but they eventually beat him down to the point that his regeneration wasn't helping much. Then things got nasty, with one of the character's being influenced by the evil artifact she put in her head, and attacking the rest of the party. One series of scraps later, the session ends with the dwarf trying a little amateur surgery, and he teleporting across the continent to tell the Elven king a few interesting things. I love my job. :) Wednesday was equally icky, what with my character pretty much losing a leg to a monstrous Thing. Yeah, like that's going to help him stay stable. :) Buckets of Dice this weekend, though I won't be able to attend all of it because of work. :( Which reminds me, I should go finish my one-off.

I'm getting more and more intimidated by the scope my next campaign will take.  Not so much the campaign itself, although it will be more detailed than the others I've run, but in that I will be rewriting the rules, and have just realised that I will have to overhaul the magic system to cobble together something like Unearthed Arcana.

What I really need is someone to help me with it.  Someone to write (type) down my stream of conciousness into a coherent and understandable format.  A Co-GM or Assitant GM type person.  Hmmm.

I also want to get any potential players together at some point to go through what I have of the rules, and start making up characters, and more importantly, backgrounds and such to fit into the world.  It would be cool if I could get them all together at the same time, make and afternoon of it, and just work together to create a workable party.

Hmmm.

All up I suppose it was a pretty good 48.  I got to dance to some good music, talk to some good people, get kissed by an attractive young woman, dance with another attractive young woman, and get nicely toasted drunk.

I rather enjoyed myself at the party last night, and without alcohol.  Woohoo.

The slave auction was rather disappointing in the end as all the people I would have bided on were snapped up by one large spender.  I think he must have spent about a thousand dollars all up.  How the freg is the little guy supposed to get some slavery goodness?

The music was okay for the start, but got pretty damn good when it got interfered with.  Not necesarily songs I would pick myself, but ones I could dance to.  And I really needed a good dance since I had been feeling antsy and hyperactive all day.

I probably would have stayed for another hour or two if I didn't have to go to work the next day.

Thanks to <lj user="pepetto"> for the offer of the umbrella, and big thanks to <lj user="the_legionnaire">, <lj user="el_gremmo">  and Brian for making sure I got a lift home.

Well I start my new hours today.  8-5 with an hour for lunch, Monday to Thursday, then 9-6 with an hour for lunch Sunday.  Pretty good hours really, though I won't be able to do any late night partying on Saturdays anymore.

Speaking of parties, the Perversion Party was... Ok.  Being the Dollshouse with the amount of people that showed up it was of course crowded as heck.  There was almost zero air flow on the dance floor, making it sweat central.  On the other hand almost all the songs I requested were played (even if I didn't get to dance to each entire song, see aforementioned crowding), and I got to talk to people more than I usually do at parties.  Also this year I had a real perversion, even if I didn't have the courage to go around acting it out.

So yeah, overall it was... Ok.

"I want you to want me, I need you to need me"

I've been promoted at work.  From monday I will no longer be a checkout chick or a trolley boy.  I will instead be working in the wine and beer section.  Yay for me.

Had a rather emotionally charged session of Invasion tonight.  There was betrayl, godly chats, attempts at redemption, entry into the service of a power, and the heroic battles of Ysgard.  Somewhere in there was a roleplaying session.

"Give me my book"

Well I didn't get to run my Gods of the New Land 2 campaign, but i'm in a game instead, which is better from my current point of view (not having to run two campaigns, finally playing DnD again).

I'm now playing in Michael's Arcanna Unearthed game, as a rather rough and tumble Mage blade.  Just got to nut out the character a bit more, write up a backstory, and I'll be ready for next tuesday.

"Bring it"

Rather eclectic session last night. Everyone seemed distracted or bored, and there was lots of time wasted with various things. I must admit though, it was fun watching the high level adventurers almost stumped by how to cross the underground swamp.
